    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-06T17:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-06T17:36:00-05:00" n="92"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-06T16:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 7, 12 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 28, 12 noon [<hi rend="italic">10 a.m.</hi>]<note n="91"
                        xml:id="d92fn91">
                        <ref target="frus1917#pg_794">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 794</ref>.</note> Yesterday afternoon
                    presented to President Cabrera the information that Honduranean Government had
                    accepted neutral zone and that Honduranean troops would be withdrawn therefrom
                    upon Guatemala withdrawing hers, and outlined to him the extent of the mutual
                    withdrawal. President accepted immediately. He informs me his withdrawal can be
                    accomplished by January 6, but I do not believe the present conditions will
                    permit such a movement. Will keep Department informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
